{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0b4f74ea-e905-4b57-b4b1-3e4b008d3bba","content":"Here's what I found in `my_app/views.py`:\n\n**Line 3** — `datetime.now()`\nThis is a direct static call that's hard to mock in tests. It tightly couples the view to wall-clock time, making time-dependent behavior difficult to verify.\n\n### Recommendation\n\nUse **`django.utils.timezone.now()`** (which is the Django-idiomatic approach and timezone-aware), and inject or mock it in tests via `unittest.mock.patch` or the [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) library.\n\nFor example:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThen in tests you can freeze time easily:\n\n```python\nfrom freezegun import freeze_time\n\n@freeze_time(\"2026-04-24\")\ndef test_index(self):\n    ...\n```\n\nThat's the only file in the project — just the one hit. The codebase is small, so the fix is quick. Want me to apply it?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3f7a99d8-1cc9-4286-923b-24e2b252d717","outputTokens":269,"requestId":"083A:B0AF0:54D8D6:6404BE:69EAD437"},"id":"1398113b-c0dc-4a69-b630-ebb692cafe75","timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:23:57.668Z","parentId":"916b72fc-fe29-487c-be11-6110ee0dea34"}
